<html>
   <head>
      <script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
      <%= stylesheet_link_tag "timeline"%>
      
      <style type="text/css">
         #mainBody {
            background: #000;
            color: #FFF;
         }
         
         #mainTitle {
            display: table;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            
            font-size: 60px;
            font-family: "Times New Roman";
            letter-spacing: 10px;
         }
         
         .textBox {
            width: 800px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            font-size: 18px;
            text-align: justify;
         }
         
         .textBoxTitle {
            text-align: center;
            font-size:24px;
         }
         .textBoxTitle:hover {
            cursor: pointer;
         }
         
         .close {
            float: right;
            color: #BBB;
            font-size: 14px;
            cursor: pointer;
         }
         
         .timeline {
            padding-top: 40px;
            padding-bottom: 20px;
         }
         
         .timeline .event {
            background-color: black;
            color: white;
         }
      </style>
   </head>
   
   
   <body id="mainBody">
      <br>
      <div id="header">
         <div id="mainTitle">Debating Motions of the Past</div>
      </div>
      
      <br><br><br>
            
      <div class="textBox" id="about">
         <div class="textBoxTitle" id="aboutTitle">About</div>
         <div id="description" style="display:none">
            Below is a collections of motions that were found in the 
            archives of the <a href=http://dukedebate.org>Duke University 
            Debating Society</a>. They remind 
            us of the issues that were debated in those years - a time 
            which was politically and socially very different. Between 
            ... and ... Duke Debate was doing the ... code of debating 
            which use one motion for the whole season.
            <span class="close" id="closeDesc">[close]</span>
         </div>
         
         <script>
            $("#aboutTitle").click(function() {
               $("#description").toggle(500);
            });
            
            $("#closeDesc").click(function() {
               $("#description").toggle(500);
            });
         </script>
      </div>
      
      <br><br>
      
      <ul class="timeline">
         <li class="event offset-first">
            1994 - THW bank bang.
         </li>
         <li class="event">
            1994 - THW bank bang.
         </li>
         <li class="event">
            1994 - THW bank bang.
         </li>
         <li class="event">
            1994 - THW bank bang.
         </li>
      </ul>
      
      <br><br>
      
      <div class="textBox" id="appeal">
            <div class="textBoxTitle" id="appealTitle">I have some antique motions...</div>
            <div id="appealDesc" style="display:none">
               If your society has antique motions that you would like 
               to contribute to this website then please contact 
               julianborrey[at]gmail.com. There are plans to expand this 
               small digital museum so that old motions from unviersities 
               all over the worlds can be viewed. Seeing topics from the 
               same decade but from different countries could be interesting.
               <span class="close" id="closeAppeal">[close]</span>
            </div>
            
            <script>
               $("#appealTitle").click(function() {
                  $("#appealDesc").toggle(500);
               });
               
               $("#closeAppeal").click(function() {
                  $("#appealDesc").toggle(500);
               });
            </script>
      </div>
   
   </body>

</html>
